summary: An ordinance amending section 12 of Ordinance No. 27700 entitled: "An ordinance relating to the use and occupation of market places in the City of Seattle, prescribing rules and regulations for the conduct thereof, providing penalties for violation and repealing all ordinances or parts of ordinances in conflict herewith" approved August 8, 1911, for the purpose of reducing the charges to farmers and others at market places.
